    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If I understand correctly, what you want is the following (the opposite of dropping is *selecting*):\r\n```\r\n>>> df[['B', 'C']]  # equivalently df.loc[:, ['B', 'C']]\r\n   B   C\r\n0  1   2\r\n1  5   6\r\n2  9  10\r\n```\r\nIn the second notation, you can even do something called \"slicing\" (notice how all the columns between start and end -- in this case `C` -- are also part of the result):\r\n```\r\n>>> df.loc[:, 'B':'D']\r\n   B   C   D\r\n0  1   2   3\r\n1  5   6   7\r\n2  9  10  11\r\n```\r\n\r\nMore info (much more) here: https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/indexing.html"
  },
